<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,568,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,343,1890,1916]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">Field notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[352,558,1891,1916]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Lasiopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leleji">
<emphasis box="[352,558,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">Lasiopogon leleji</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits South Korean east coast beaches backed by young pines. Mating pairs observed were in copulation for 
<number box="[598,695,1930,1956]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" value="15.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="10.0">10 to 20</number>
seconds before separating from their tail-to-tail position. They are cannibalistic (male feeding on male), and also prey on 
<taxonomicName box="[844,932,1970,1996]" kingdom="Plantae" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[948,1067,1970,1996]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Muscidae</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName box="[1079,1236,1970,1996]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Bombyliidae</taxonomicName>
). See 
<tableCitation box="[1306,1394,1970,1996]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,239,276,300]" captionText="TABLE 1. Summary of seasonality and prey of asilids reported in this paper" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
Table 
<number box="[1379,1394,1970,1996]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" value="1.0">1</number>
</tableCitation>
for prey and seasonality.
</paragraph>
